stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> idle: createDeployment({ host })

  idle --> planning: deploy()
  planning --> failed: plan invalid (DeploymentPlanError)
  planning --> deploying: plan.ok

  deploying --> verifying: release strategy completed
  deploying --> failed: strategy failed (DeploymentExecutionError)

  verifying --> deployed: verification passed
  verifying --> failed: verification failed (DeploymentVerificationError)

  failed --> rolling_back: automatic rollback (unless autoRollback:false)
  deployed --> rolling_back: rollback() (manual/partial/full)
  rolling_back --> rolled_back: rollback verified
  rolling_back --> failed: rollback verification failed (RollbackError)

  deployed --> [*]
  rolled_back --> [*]

  note right of deploying
    Release strategy (injected, deterministic):
      immediate → deploy, verify
      rolling   → deploy, verify × N waves
      blue-green→ deploy green, verify, switch (blue retained)
      canary    → deploy, verify at each stage %
    Each drives the ops facade (deploy/health/undeploy) → Host Runtime.
  end note

  note right of verifying
    §8 checks: plan completed · host healthy · runtime healthy ·
    all services healthy · compatibility passed · strategy completed.
  end note

  note right of rolling_back
    Restores the retained previous version through the host,
    reusing ADR-040 lifecycle transitively (ADR-044 → ADR-043 → ADR-040).
  end note
